# Trivy CVE exceptions for orkyo-community
#
# Format:
#   CVE-YYYY-NNNNN  # Impact | Reason | Added: YYYY-MM-DD | Review: YYYY-MM-DD
#
# Policy: time-bound only. Review date must be within 14 days of added date.
# Remove entries once the upstream fix is available.

# ── nginx:1.28-alpine — Alpine 3.23 packages not yet rebuilt by nginx upstream ──
# Fix versions exist in Alpine 3.23 but nginx has not published a new 1.28-alpine
# image that includes them. nightly security-refresh.yml will auto-resolve once
# nginx rebuilds. Review: check if nginx:1.28-alpine digest has changed.

# openssl 3.5.5-r0 → 3.5.6-r0
CVE-2026-31789  # CRITICAL | openssl: heap buffer overflow on 32-bit systems in X.509 cert | Fix in Alpine 3.23 (3.5.6-r0); nginx:1.28-alpine not yet rebuilt | Added: 2026-05-21 | Review: 2026-06-04
CVE-2026-28387  # HIGH | openssl: use-after-free in DANE TLSA auth | Fix in Alpine 3.23 (3.5.6-r0); nginx:1.28-alpine not yet rebuilt | Added: 2026-05-21 | Review: 2026-06-04
CVE-2026-28388  # HIGH | openssl: NULL pointer dereference in delta CRL | Fix in Alpine 3.23 (3.5.6-r0); nginx:1.28-alpine not yet rebuilt | Added: 2026-05-21 | Review: 2026-06-04
CVE-2026-28389  # HIGH | openssl: DoS in CMS processing | Fix in Alpine 3.23 (3.5.6-r0); nginx:1.28-alpine not yet rebuilt | Added: 2026-05-21 | Review: 2026-06-04
CVE-2026-28390  # HIGH | openssl: NULL pointer dereference in CMS | Fix in Alpine 3.23 (3.5.6-r0); nginx:1.28-alpine not yet rebuilt | Added: 2026-05-21 | Review: 2026-06-04

